<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-352] Throw exception to client if it makes a produce/consume request to a Kafka broker for a topic that hasn&apos;t been created</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-352</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It will be good to inform the client if it makes a produce/consume request to a Kafka broker for a topic that hasn&apos;t been created. The exception should be something like UnknownTopicException that is descriptive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
